  Locus:
    Page: 173
    Verse: 8
Tags:
  - Freedom
---
Who, then, is free? The wise man who commands his passions, who fears not
want, nor death, nor chains, firmly resisting his appetites and despising
the honors of the world, who relies wholly on himself.
